````` ::: ::: The dataset is split into a test and a training set. ::: {.cell hash='06_deep_learning_challenge_cache/html/unnamed-chunk-3_6092517e8f62199e6d8f965d0626ef85'} ```{.r .cell-code} # Split test/training sets set.seed(69) train_test_split <- initial_split(churn_data_tbl, prop = 0.8) train_test_split ``` ::: {.cell-output .cell-output-stdout} ``` #> #> <5625/1407/7032> ``` ::: ```{.r .cell-code} # Retrieve train and test sets train_tbl <- training(train_test_split) test_tbl <- testing(train_test_split) ``` ::: ::: {.cell hash='06_deep_learning_challenge_cache/html/unnamed-chunk-4_853471f39e222578567dc64cffafb1fc'} ```{.r .cell-code} churn_data_tbl %>% ggplot(aes(x = tenure)) + geom_histogram(bins = 6, color = "white", fill = "#2DC6D6") + labs( title = "Tenure Counts With Six Bins", x = "tenure (month)" ) ``` ::: {.cell-output-display} ![](06_deep_learning_challenge_files/figure-html/unnamed-chunk-4-1.png){width=672} ::: ```{.r .cell-code} train_tbl %>% select(Churn, TotalCharges) %>% mutate( Churn = Churn %>% as.factor() %>% as.numeric(), LogTotalCharges = log(TotalCharges) ) %>% correlate() %>% focus(Churn) %>% fashion() ``` ::: {.cell-output .cell-output-stderr} ``` #> Correlation computed with #> * Method: 'pearson' #> * Missing treated using: 'pairwise.complete.obs' ``` ::: ::: {.cell-output-display} `````{=html}
````` ::: ::: ##One-Hot Encoding ::: {.cell hash='06_deep_learning_challenge_cache/html/unnamed-chunk-5_c9d8d1c49db638461dcd917ae3cb85e1'} ```{.r .cell-code} churn_data_tbl %>% pivot_longer(cols = c(Contract, InternetService, MultipleLines, PaymentMethod), names_to = "feature", values_to = "category") %>% ggplot(aes(category)) + geom_bar(fill = "#2DC6D6") + facet_wrap(~ feature, scales = "free") + labs( title = "Features with multiple categories: Need to be one-hot encoded" ) + theme(axis.text.x = element_text(angle = 25, hjust = 1)) ``` ::: {.cell-output-display} ![](06_deep_learning_challenge_files/figure-html/unnamed-chunk-5-1.png){width=672} ::: ::: #Proprocessing the Data ::: {.cell hash='06_deep_learning_challenge_cache/html/unnamed-chunk-6_2b57f29e5e806ba0f3fcc1605d89d92c'} ```{.r .cell-code} rec_obj <- recipe(Churn ~ ., data = train_tbl) %>% step_rm(Churn) %>% step_discretize(tenure, options = list(cuts = 6)) %>% step_log(TotalCharges) %>% step_dummy(all_nominal(), -all_outcomes(), one_hot = T) %>% step_center(all_predictors(), -all_outcomes()) %>% step_scale(all_predictors(), -all_outcomes()) %>% prep(data = train_tbl) ``` ::: #Bake the predictors ::: {.cell hash='06_deep_learning_challenge_cache/html/unnamed-chunk-7_0b88242a17b8f5399eed2f445549a0ed'} ```{.r .cell-code} # Bake the predictors x_train_tbl <- bake(rec_obj, new_data = train_tbl) x_test_tbl <- bake(rec_obj, new_data = test_tbl) ``` ::: #Response Variables for training and testing set ::: {.cell hash='06_deep_learning_challenge_cache/html/unnamed-chunk-8_d2738a2ec2a790198fe62999f76f3bb0'} ```{.r .cell-code} # Response variables for training and testing sets y_train_vec <- ifelse(train_tbl$Churn == "Yes", 1, 0) y_test_vec <- ifelse(test_tbl$Churn == "Yes", 1, 0) ``` ::: #Building the AI Model ::: {.cell hash='06_deep_learning_challenge_cache/html/unnamed-chunk-9_b87f68945878e4345789aee9f2d102b8'} ```{.r .cell-code} # Building our Artificial Neural Network model_keras <- keras_model_sequential() model_keras %>% # First hidden layer layer_dense( units = 16, kernel_initializer = "uniform", activation = "relu", input_shape = ncol(x_train_tbl)) %>% # Dropout to prevent overfitting layer_dropout(rate = 0.1) %>% # Second hidden layer layer_dense( units = 16, kernel_initializer = "uniform", activation = "relu") %>% # Dropout to prevent overfitting layer_dropout(rate = 0.1) %>% # Output layer layer_dense( units = 1, kernel_initializer = "uniform", activation = "sigmoid") %>% # Compile ANN compile( optimizer = 'adam', loss = 'binary_crossentropy', metrics = c('accuracy') ) model_keras ``` ::: {.cell-output .cell-output-stdout} ``` #> Model: "sequential" #> ________________________________________________________________________________ #> Layer (type) Output Shape Param # #> ================================================================================ #> dense_2 (Dense) (None, 16) 816 #> dropout_1 (Dropout) (None, 16) 0 #> dense_1 (Dense) (None, 16) 272 #> dropout (Dropout) (None, 16) 0 #> dense (Dense) (None, 1) 17 #> ================================================================================ #> Total params: 1,105 #> Trainable params: 1,105 #> Non-trainable params: 0 #> ________________________________________________________________________________ ``` ::: ::: # Fit the keras model to the training data ::: {.cell hash='06_deep_learning_challenge_cache/html/unnamed-chunk-10_101c8be6e1fce194eb811ccf07d4976a'} ```{.r .cell-code} x_train_matrix = as.matrix(x_train_tbl) y_train_matrix = as.matrix(y_train_vec) x_test_matrix = as.matrix(x_test_tbl) y_test_matrix = as.matrix(y_test_vec) fit_keras <- fit( model_keras, x = x_train_matrix, y = y_train_matrix, epochs = 35, batch_size = 50, validation_data = list(x_test_matrix, y_test_matrix), validation_split = 0.3 ) fit_keras ``` ::: {.cell-output .cell-output-stdout} ``` #> #> Final epoch (plot to see history): #> loss: 0.393 #> accuracy: 0.8215 #> val_loss: 0.4216 #> val_accuracy: 0.796 ``` ::: ::: ##Plotting of the training/validation accuracy ::: {.cell hash='06_deep_learning_challenge_cache/html/unnamed-chunk-11_50203dbdb4d6c2b7ef8e71c235ae9a76'} ```{.r .cell-code} # Plot the training/validation history of our Keras model #plot(fit_keras) + # labs(title = "Deep Learning Training Results") + # theme(legend.position = "bottom", # strip.placement = "inside", # strip.background = element_rect(fill = "#grey")) ``` ::: #Predictions ::: {.cell hash='06_deep_learning_challenge_cache/html/unnamed-chunk-12_e67ec73d9b9d11adddf518b0bd672a82'} ```{.r .cell-code} # Predicted Class yhat_keras_class_vec <- predict(model_keras, as.matrix(x_test_tbl)) %>% as.vector() %>% round() # Predicted Class Probability yhat_keras_prob_vec <- predict(model_keras, as.matrix(x_test_tbl)) %>% as.vector() ``` ::: # Estimations ::: {.cell hash='06_deep_learning_challenge_cache/html/unnamed-chunk-13_78ef775c159ca0e127d399cb54e8fb14'} ```{.r .cell-code} estimates_keras_tbl <- tibble( truth = as.factor(y_test_vec) %>% fct_recode(Yes = "1", No = "0"), estimate = as.factor(yhat_keras_class_vec) %>% fct_recode(Yes = "1", No = "0"), class_prob = yhat_keras_prob_vec ) estimates_keras_tbl ``` ::: {.cell-output-display} `````{=html}
````` ::: ::: ##confusion Table ::: {.cell hash='06_deep_learning_challenge_cache/html/unnamed-chunk-14_4570873bbc8b10995ff1e482140b35c1'} ```{.r .cell-code} # Confusion Table confusion_table <- conf_mat(data = estimates_keras_tbl, truth, estimate) confusion_table ``` ::: {.cell-output .cell-output-stdout} ``` #> Truth #> Prediction No Yes #> No 936 165 #> Yes 122 184 ``` ::: ```{.r .cell-code} # Accuracy accuracy_result <- accuracy(data = estimates_keras_tbl, truth, estimate) accuracy_result ``` ::: {.cell-output-display} `````{=html}
````` ::: ```{.r .cell-code} # AUC auc_result <- roc_auc(data = estimates_keras_tbl, truth, class_prob, event_level = "second") auc_result ``` ::: {.cell-output-display} `````{=html}
````` ::: ::: # Precision ::: {.cell hash='06_deep_learning_challenge_cache/html/unnamed-chunk-15_4c7d71416ef0b11b55c0814ab8294795'} ```{.r .cell-code} # Precision precision_result <- precision(data = estimates_keras_tbl, truth, estimate) # Recall recall_result <- recall(data = estimates_keras_tbl, truth, estimate) # Combine precision and recall results into a tibble precision_recall_tbl <- tibble( precision = precision_result$.estimate, recall = recall_result$.estimate ) precision_recall_tbl ``` ::: {.cell-output-display} `````{=html}
````` ::: ```{.r .cell-code} # F1-Statistic estimates_keras_tbl %>% f_meas(truth, estimate, beta = 1) ``` ::: {.cell-output-display} `````{=html}

````` ::: ```{.r .cell-code} # Setup lime::model_type() function for keras model_type.keras.engine.sequential.Sequential <- function(x, ...) { return("classification") } # Setup lime::predict_model() function for keras predict_model.keras.engine.sequential.Sequential <- function(x, newdata, type, ...) { pred <- predict(object = x, x = as.matrix(newdata)) return(data.frame(Yes = pred, No = 1 - pred)) } library(lime) # Test our predict_model() function predict_model(x = model_keras, newdata = x_test_tbl, type = 'raw') %>% tibble::as_tibble() ``` ::: {.cell-output-display} `````{=html}
